<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Correct" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Correct,</orth> vb. 1) to set right, to counteract whatever is injurious: <emph>whose</emph> (the sun's) <cit><quote>medicinable eye --s the ill aspects of planets evil,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.92" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 92</bibl></cit>. Absolutely: <cit><quote>where some, like magistrates, c. at home,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.191" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 191</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to chastise: <bibl n="shak. son 111.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 111, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.87" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 2, 87</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.331" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 331</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.87" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 87</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.2.5" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 2, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.202" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 3, 202</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.335" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 335</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.6.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 6, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.2.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 2, 78</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.3.57" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.3.23" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 3, 23</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>